<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-057-038 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 362 141</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 20 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>BellSouth makes mobile service moves.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   BellSouth Corp. (Services).andO;Ticker:    BLS.andO;Topic:     Pager SystemsBusiness PlanningBell Regional Holding CompaniesTelephone companiesCellular radio.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BELLSOUTH MAKES MOBILE SERVICE MOVES 09/20/91 ATLANTA, GEORGIA, U.S.A., 1991SEP 20 (NB) -- BellSouth moved to compete head-on with MTel's new Skywordpaging service, and signed a deal with Cellular Technical Services of Seattlefor a system to add credit limits to its cellular phone operations.andM;BellSouth's MobileComm unit, like MTel itself, is based in Jackson,Mississippi.andP;  The new service, called MobileComm Nationwide Messaging, willbe inaugurated at a ceremony in Atlanta's Inforum trade center September 28.andO;Like MTel's system, MobileComm will offer short text messages to pagingsubscribers, taking advantage of a new Motorola pager called the Advisorwhich offers an 80-character screen.andP;  Unlike MTel, however, BellSouth'soffering can be broken down into one or more of 5 regions.andP;  MTel's Skywordmust be bought nationally.andM;The new messaging feature also offers a personal greeting from the person whowill receive the message, and sequentially numbers all messages sent, sousers know if they may have missed any messages.andP;  Finally, MobileComm allowscustomers to use one toll- free phone number to access digital paging, voicemail, and all basic services, eliminating the need for callers to remembertwo separate 800 numbers.andM;The new service intensifies competition between MTel and BellSouth.andO;Ironically, MTel decided to concentrate on its SkyTel nationwide pagingoperation after selling its cellular operations to BellSouth a few years ago.andM;Also, BellSouth's Cellular operations joined a number of other carriers,including LIN Broadcasting and American Cellular Communications, in using theHotwatch System of Cellular Technical Services in Seattle.andP;  Hotwatch is asoftware system which permits carriers to set subscriber-specific creditlimits on callers.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910919/Press Contact: MobileComm, Jean Coppenbarger,1-800-685-5555)</TEXT></DOC>